node.text: Having a growing little one means their appetite is growing, too! Check out our recommendations for keeping up with your baby’s developing feeding habits. 👶

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Owlet on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'month by month baby feeding guide'.

Photo by Owlet on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '0-4 Months Old Recommended Food: Breastmilk or formula Readiness Indicator: The AAP recommends breastmilk or formula ONLY for Baby's first few months.'.

Photo by Owlet on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4-6 Months Old Recommended Food: Try pureed fruits & veggies, pureed meat and semi-liquid cereal. Readiness Indicator: Sits up with good head control & opens mouth eager to eat.'.

Photo by Owlet on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '6-8 Months Old Recommended Food: You can now introduce strained fruits & veggies Readiness Indicator: Sit up with good head control & opens mouth eager to eat.'.

Photo by Owlet on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '8-10 Months Old :น. Recommended Food: Small pieces of meat & soft finger foods like cereal, pieces of pasta and wafer-like crackers. Readiness Indicator: Baby picks up objects with thumb & forefinger and chews on everything.'.

Photo by Owlet on September 13, 2021. May be an image of text that says '10-12 Months Old ለAI Recommended Food: Introduce soft fruits &veggies cut into small pieces and even scrambled eggs. Readiness Indicator: Baby is attempting to use a spoon, growing more teeth, & swallowing easier.'.
Photo shared by Owlet on September 12, 2021 tagging @asaltylifeforus. May be an image of baby and indoor.

Jen (@asaltylifeforus) and her family can sleep peacefully thanks to reassurance from the Owlet Monitor Duo! ✨

"Pippa is always SO happy when she first wakes up! So when I see that she is awake through our @owletcare Cam, I come running. I love the Owlet Smart Sock, but honestly their Cam is just as amazing - it has two-way audio, sound and motion notifications (my fave), and 1080p with night vision. You don’t need the Smart Sock to have the Cam and it’s so easy to use through their app!" - @haileydevine

We all deserve a wake up call as cute as this! 🥰

Follow the link in our bio to shop the Cam and other award-winning Owlet monitors.
